# Modular Design — {{PROJECT_NAME}}

## Principle

Each module has a single responsibility and owns its domain.
Modules communicate through well-defined contracts (typed models or interfaces),
not by reaching into each other's internals.

**Rule:** No module imports directly from another business module.
All cross-module communication goes through models or the routes/controller layer.

---

## Module map

```
{{PROJECT_NAME}}/
├── core/
│   ├── auth          — identity, sessions, API keys
│   ├── models        — shared data models / DB schema
│   └── payments      — unified payment webhook handler
│
├── {{product_1}}/
│   ├── {{layer_1}}   — {{description}}
│   ├── {{layer_2}}   — {{description}}
│   └── routes        — HTTP endpoints
│
├── {{product_2}}/
│   ├── evaluator     — core business logic
│   ├── policies/     — one file per rule variant
│   │   ├── base      — BasePolicy contract + result type
│   │   ├── registry  — ACTIVE_POLICIES list
│   │   └── <name>    — per-variant implementation
│   ├── models        — input/output types
│   └── routes        — HTTP endpoints
│
└── admin/
    └── routes        — admin panel (metrics, users, revenue)
```

